<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The enum of section identifiers to be used in internal interfaces.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Pre-standard implementation of package files defined a number of section</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><Highlight kind="comment">/// identifiers with values that clash definitions in the DWARFv5 standard.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><Highlight kind="comment">/// See https://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/DebugFissionDWP and Section 7.3.5.3 in DWARFv5.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The following identifiers are the same in the proposal and in DWARFv5:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;INFO         = 1 (.debug&#95;info.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;ABBREV       = 3 (.debug&#95;abbrev.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;LINE         = 4 (.debug&#95;line.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;STR&#95;OFFSETS  = 6 (.debug&#95;str&#95;offsets.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The following identifiers are defined only in DWARFv5:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;LOCLISTS     = 5 (.debug&#95;loclists.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;RNGLISTS     = 8 (.debug&#95;rnglists.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The following identifiers are defined only in the GNU proposal:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;TYPES        = 2 (.debug&#95;types.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;LOC          = 5 (.debug&#95;loc.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - DW&#95;SECT&#95;MACINFO      = 7 (.debug&#95;macinfo.dwo)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DW&#95;SECT&#95;MACRO for the .debug&#95;macro.dwo section is defined in both standards,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><Highlight kind="comment">/// but with different values, 8 in GNU and 7 in DWARFv5.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This enum defines constants to represent the identifiers of both sets.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For DWARFv5 ones, the values are the same as defined in the standard.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For pre-standard ones that correspond to sections being deprecated in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DWARFv5, the values are chosen arbitrary and a tag &quot;&#95;EXT&#95;&quot; is added to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the names.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The enum is for internal use only. The user should not expect the values</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to correspond to any input/output constants. Special conversion functions,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><Highlight kind="comment">/// serializeSectionKind() and deserializeSectionKind(), should be used for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the translation.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
